abstract: Damon Lindelof, creator of the HBO comic adaptation, and Regina King, its star, discuss why the show is a Rorschach test of its own.
snippet: Damon Lindelof, creator of the HBO comic adaptation, and Regina King, its star, discuss why the show is a Rorschach test of its own.
lead_paragraph: The chapters of “Watchmen” are marked by illustrations of a clock ticking toward an apocalypse. But on a recent morning, Damon Lindelof, who just adapted the influential comic for HBO, was focused on a different countdown.

abstract: The Portal Bridge is one of the busiest rail bridges in the country. But when it opens it often gets stuck, paralyzing train traffic.
snippet: The Portal Bridge is one of the busiest rail bridges in the country. But when it opens it often gets stuck, paralyzing train traffic.
lead_paragraph: It is a fairly ordinary bridge, not too long and not very tall. But the Portal Bridge’s modest profile obscures its vital role: It is a main rail link between New York City and most of the rest of the country.

abstract: Elizabeth Warren was called out by rivals for a change, Joe Biden failed to stand out and Bernie Sanders calmed concerns about his health. Pete Buttigieg had his biggest night yet.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren was called out by rivals for a change, Joe Biden failed to stand out and Bernie Sanders calmed concerns about his health. Pete Buttigieg had his biggest night yet.
lead_paragraph: WESTERVILLE, Ohio — The CNN/New York Times debate on Tuesday night revealed new dynamics in the Democratic presidential race: Senator Elizabeth Warren took sustained fire from multiple rivals, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. struggled to make an impact and Mayor Pete Buttigieg and other candidates were newly aggressive in making their points.

abstract: Twelve Democratic candidates for president gathered in Ohio for the debate hosted by CNN and The New York Times. Here were the highlights from the night.
snippet: Twelve Democratic candidates for president gathered in Ohio for the debate hosted by CNN and The New York Times. Here were the highlights from the night.
lead_paragraph: Tuesday’s CNN/New York Times debate in Ohio featured 12 candidates: Joe Biden, Elizabeth Warren, Bernie Sanders, Kamala Harris, Pete Buttigieg, Cory Booker, Amy Klobuchar, Andrew Yang, Beto O’Rourke, Julián Castro, Tulsi Gabbard and Tom Steyer.
headline_main: Top Video Moments From the Democratic Presidential Debate

abstract: Twelve Democratic presidential candidates shared the stage in Ohio for the fourth televised primary debate.
snippet: Twelve Democratic presidential candidates shared the stage in Ohio for the fourth televised primary debate.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris of California made an impassioned plea on Tuesday for her fellow presidential candidates to focus on women’s access to reproductive health care, generating applause.

abstract: The criticism of Elizabeth Warren illustrated her status as an emerging front-runner, while Joe Biden faced scrutiny over his son’s financial dealings overseas.
snippet: The criticism of Elizabeth Warren illustrated her status as an emerging front-runner, while Joe Biden faced scrutiny over his son’s financial dealings overseas.
lead_paragraph: WESTERVILLE, Ohio — Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts faced a sustained barrage of criticism from her Democratic rivals at a presidential debate in Ohio on Tuesday, tangling with a group of underdog moderates who assailed her liberal economic proposals, while former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. appeared to fade from the fray after parrying President Trump’s attacks on his family.
